hands_on_practices.problem:
Consider a one-dimensional lattice of spin-$ rac{1}{2}$ fermions with lattice spacing $a_0$ and on-site repulsion described by the Hubbard interaction $U \sum_{j} n_{j\uparrow} n_{j\downarrow}$, at or very near half filling. In the continuum limit, represent the low-energy fermion degrees of freedom in terms of right- and left-moving fields and bosonize the theory using the standard spin-charge separation into charge and spin bosonic fields $\phi_c$, $	heta_c$, $\phi_s$, and $	heta_s$. Adopt the conventional Tomonaga-Luttinger Liquid (TLL) normalization in which each sector is described by a Gaussian Hamiltonian of the form $H_{
