u}(y)] = i \pi \delta(x-y)$. Assume spin-rotational invariance so that $K_s = 1$.

Starting from the bosonized expression of the local densities $n_{\sigma}(x)$, and retaining the most relevant non-linear harmonics generated by the on-site interaction near half filling, do the following:
- Derive the leading non-linear cosine terms that appear in the bosonized interaction in the charge and spin sectors.
- Identify explicitly the umklapp scattering term in the charge sector that becomes allowed at half filling, and write it in terms of the charge boson $\phi_c$.
- Compute the scaling dimension $\Delta_u$ of this umklapp operator as a function of the charge-sector Luttinger parameter $K_c$ using the Gaussian fixed-point correlators implied by the TLL Hamiltonian.
- Using the Renormalization Group (RG) criterion that an operator is relevant when its scaling dimension satisfies $\Delta < 2$, determine the critical value $K_c^{\star}$ at which the umklapp operator becomes marginal and a Mott gap begins to open in the charge sector for repulsive interactions.

Your final reported answer must be the single exact value of $K_c^{\star}$, with no units. If you introduce any numerical approximations, round your answer to four significant figures, but exact symbolic values are preferred and acceptable.
